    <summary>CLI wrapper for Wheels MVC framework powered by LuCLI</summary>
    <description><![CDATA[
The Wheels CLI provides a convenient `wheels` command for the Wheels MVC framework, powered by LuCLI.

## Usage
After installation, use commands like:
- `wheels generate model User`
- `wheels migrate up`
- `wheels server start`
- `wheels --help`

All arguments are passed through to `lucli wheels`.

## Prerequisites
- LuCLI must be installed and available in your PATH
- Install LuCLI via: `choco install lucli`

## What's New in 2.0
- Powered by LuCLI instead of CommandBox
- Native CLI argument handling (no conversion needed)
- Built-in MCP server support for AI-assisted development
- Dramatically simpler wrapper (standard CLI conventions)
]]></description>
    <releaseNotes>Major: switched backend from CommandBox to LuCLI. Simplified wrapper scripts. Added MCP support.</releaseNotes>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency id="lucli" version="1.0.0" />
    </dependencies>
  </metadata>
  <files>
    <file src="tools\**" target="tools" />
  </files>
